# 🧠 JWebMP Website Repository Rules for AI Agents

These rules provide specific context for AI agents (Copilot, Cursor, etc.) working on this repository to ensure consistency with the technology stack and architectural patterns.

## 🛠️ Technology Stack
- **Language**: Java 25 (with latest preview features).
- **Build Tool**: Maven.
- **Frameworks**: GuicedEE, Guice, Vert.x 5, JWebMP, WebAwesome.
- **Architecture**: Modular JPMS services with dual-registered SPIs (`module-info.java` + `META-INF/services/`).

## 🏗️ Architectural Constraints
- **Forward-only Changes**: Never delete existing functionality unless explicitly asked.
- **Single Boot**: The site uses a single `Boot.main()` entry point with `IGuiceContext.inject()`.
- **Static Catalogs**: Plugin and template catalogs are statically defined in Java — no filesystem scanning at runtime.
- **WebAwesome Layout**: All pages extend `WebsitePage` which uses `WaPage` for consistent menu, header, footer, and navigation.
- **Angular Generation**: Components use `@NgComponent` and `@NgRoutable` annotations; Angular code is generated at build time by the Angular Maven Plugin.

## 🎯 Prompting Guidance
- New pages should extend `WebsitePage<T>` and implement `INgComponent<T>`.
- Use `@NgComponent` with a kebab-case selector prefixed with `jwebmp-`.
- Use `@NgRoutable` for route path assignment.
- All user-visible text must be wrapped with `escapeAngular()`.
- Use shared helpers from `WebsitePage`: `headingText()`, `bodyText()`, `captionText()`, `featureCard()`, `buildSection()`, `codeBlock()`, `codeBlockWithTitle()`.

